.TH ZEROFETCH 1 "December 2025" "Zerofetch 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zerofetch \- A lightweight system information tool for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zerofetch
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B zerofetch
is a command-line system information tool written in bash that displays information about your operating system, software, and hardware in an aesthetic and visually pleasing way.
.PP
The overall purpose of Zerofetch is to be used in screenshots of your system. Zerofetch shows the information other people want to see in a clean, colorful format alongside your distribution's ASCII logo.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " \fIFILE\fR"
Use a custom configuration file instead of the default (~/.config/zerofetch/config.conf)
.TP
.BR \-\-logo " \fIDISTRO\fR"
Set the ASCII logo to display. Available options include: arch, ubuntu, debian, fedora, gentoo, and more.
.TP
.BR \-\-off
Disable the ASCII logo and display only system information
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.SH CONFIGURATION
Zerofetch can be configured via the configuration file located at:
.PP
.RS
.I ~/.config/zerofetch/config.conf
.RE
.PP
The configuration file allows you to customize:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Which information fields to display
.IP \(bu 2
Color schemes and separators
.IP \(bu 2
ASCII logo preferences
.IP \(bu 2
Output formatting options
.IP \(bu 2
Custom information fields
.RE
.PP
If no configuration file exists, Zerofetch will use sensible defaults.
.SH INFORMATION DISPLAYED
By default, Zerofetch displays:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Operating System name and version
.IP \(bu 2
Linux kernel version
.IP \(bu 2
System uptime
.IP \(bu 2
Package count (with package managers)
.IP \(bu 2
Shell type and version
.IP \(bu 2
Screen resolution
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop Environment / Window Manager
.IP \(bu 2
GTK/Qt themes and icons
.IP \(bu 2
Terminal emulator
.IP \(bu 2
CPU model and specifications
.IP \(bu 2
GPU information
.IP \(bu 2
Memory usage
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B zerofetch
Display system information with automatic distro detection
.TP
.B zerofetch \-\-logo arch
Display system information with Arch Linux logo
.TP
.B zerofetch \-\-off
Display only text information without ASCII art
.TP
.B zerofetch \-\-config ~/.zerofetch.conf
Use a custom configuration file
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/zerofetch/config.conf
User configuration file
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/zerofetch
Zerofetch executable (default installation path)
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B bash
Version 3.2 or higher
.TP
.B Linux kernel
Version 2.6 or higher
.PP
Additional features may require:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
xrandr (for screen resolution)
.IP \(bu 2
xprop (for window manager detection)
.IP \(bu 2
lspci (for GPU information)
.RE
